    <!--
        CVE-2018-1258 — spring-security-core 7.0.5 (FALSE POSITIVE)
        CVSS3: 8.8 (AV:N/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H)
        reason: FALSE POSITIVE. CVE-2018-1258 describes an authorization bypass in
                Spring Framework 5.0.5 (specifically that point release) when combined
                with any version of Spring Security. The vulnerability was fixed in
                Spring Framework 5.0.6 (released May 2018).

                OWASP Dependency-Check's CPE matcher matches the broad NVD CPE
                cpe:2.3:a:pivotal_software:spring_security:* against spring-security-core-7.0.5.jar,
                producing this false positive. The affected component is Spring Framework 5.0.5,
                NOT Spring Security 7.x.

                This project uses Spring Boot 4.0.6 which ships Spring Framework 6.x / 7.x —
                confirming this is a false positive. The CVE does not apply to any version of
                the spring-security-core artifact itself; it applies to a specific version of
                spring-framework (which is a different artifact).

                Reference: https://pivotal.io/security/cve-2018-1258
        owner: security-team
        tracking: https://github.com/jeremylong/DependencyCheck/issues (known DC false-positive pattern)
        expires: 2026-08-17
    -->
    <suppress>
        <notes>
            reason: FALSE POSITIVE. CVE-2018-1258 is a Spring Framework 5.0.5 vulnerability
                    (fixed in 5.0.6). OWASP DC CPE matcher incorrectly matches spring-security-core
                    7.x. This project runs Spring Boot 4 / Spring Framework 6+, which is unaffected.
            owner: security-team
            tracking: https://pivotal.io/security/cve-2018-1258
            expires: 2026-08-17
        </notes>
        <gav regex="true">org\.springframework\.security:spring-security-core:.*</gav>
        <cve>CVE-2018-1258</cve>
    </suppress>

